Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the use of joint probability distributions to model the mapping between input and output variables, and the use of a set of data sampled from this distribution to identify a model of the data. The paper also discusses the use of a local risk criterion to measure the fit of the model to the system, and the use of a generalisation error to measure the performance of the model. These are all characteristic features of probabilistic methods in AI.
